#Setting Up Your Development Environment

Install Node
You may go to these instructions if you're running ubuntu because the repositories don't have the latest version:
https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-node-js-on-an-ubuntu-14-04-server

sudo npm install -g bower gulp

Install ruby then install SASS
gem install sass

Install Project Dependencies
npm install
bower install

Do a gulp build for a production build
gulp build

or a gulp watch to watch files and perform live reload upon file change
gulp watch

Install the live reload chrome extension
Make sure the "Allow Access to File URLs option in live reload is set to on"

